{
  "texts": [
    "torally Kummer-faithful) if, for every finite extension L of k and every semiabelian variety (resp.",
    "every torus) A over L, the divisible part A(L) div = ∞ n=1 nA(L) of the Mordell-Weil group A(L) of A over L is trivial;",
    "A(L) div = 0.",
    "(ii) ([OT22, Definition 2.6 (2)]) A perfect field k is said to be highly Kummerfaithful if, for every finite extension L of k and every proper smooth variety X over L, it holds that",
    ") G L = 0 for any prime number ℓ ̸ = ch(k) and any i, r with i ̸ = 2r, where the suffix (-) G L means the largest quotient of (-) on which the absolute Galois group G L of L acts trivially."
  ]
}